title: Fixed #154 (crash resetting logbook) caused by a horribly inefficient method
message:
Fixed #154 (crash resetting logbook) caused by a horribly inefficient method

Basically, cleanPhotosAsync was taking upwards of 40 seconds to
complete in the background, and it uses the database.  If the logbook
was reset within those 40 seconds, the database is reset and
cleanPhotosAsync is trying to read from an old, delete database.

title: Fixed importing and exporting issue
message:
Fixed importing and exporting issue

Catch date exporting was only accurate to the minute (to keep
compatibility with iOS).  It has been updated to be accurate to a
thousandth of a second, but will still parse the old format if needed.
If there is a duplicate date as a result of the inaccurate date format,
a random 60000 ms is added to the date, then another random 60000 ms is
removed from the date.  After the alteration, the chances of duplicate
dates are basically zero.
